quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  51,7,Swear by the heaven (sky) full of paths (orbits)
  51,8,"Most surely you are in doctrines (opinions, teachings, ideologies) discordant (or inconsistent or contradictory)"
  51,9,"He is turned away by them from truth, who would be (or wishes to be) turned away"
  51,10,Cursed be the conjecturers (or lie-mongers)
  51,11,Who flounder heedless in an abyss (of ignorance and confusion)
  51,12,"They ask, \"When will be the day of judgment"
  51,13,It is the day on which they shall be tried at the Fire
  51,14,Taste you your torment! This is what you sought to hasten
  51,15,Surely those who guard (against evil) shall be in Gardens and Springs
  51,16,"Taking joy in what their Lord gives them; surely they were before that, the doers of good"
  51,17,They used to sleep but little in the night
  51,18,And in the morning they prayed for forgiveness
  51,19,"And in their wealth a portion was allotted for him who asked (the needy) and to him who was denied (the outcast, the deprived person or the one who could not ask)"
  51,20,And in the earth there are signs for those who have sure faith
  51,21,And also in your own souls; will you not then see
  51,22,And in the heaven is your sustenance and that which you are promised
  51,23,"And by the Lord of the heavens and the earth! It is most surely the truth, even as you speak"
  51,24,Has there come to you information about the honoured guests of Abraham
  51,25,"When they entered his presence they said, \"Peace. Peace.\" Said he, \"What a strange people"
  51,26,Then he turned aside to his family secretly and brought a fat (roasted) calf
  51,27,"And placed it before them. He said, \"What! Will you not eat"
  51,28,"(When they did not eat) he conceived in his mind a fear of them. They said, \"Fear not.\" And they gave him the good news of a son endowed with knowledge"
  51,29,"Then his wife came up in great grief, and she struck her face and said, \"An old barren woman"
  51,30,"They said, \"Thus says your Lord: Surely He is the Wise, the Knowing"